#Text=711chan.org administrator calls for an end to attacks on Scientology
#Text=Monday , January 28 , 2008

#Text=Administrators for 711chan.org , one of the websites responsible for starting Project Chanology , a " raid " or attack against the Church of Scientology and their website , slowed down their " attack " .
#Text=In an exclusive interview with Wikinews , an administrator of 711chan states that they will " probably stay away from the CoS [ Church of Scientology ] . "
#Text=" We 're probably just going to stay away from the CoS raid .

#Text=The rules they refer to , according to Plasma , mean the  Rules of the Internet " and are :

column1: #Text=Quote
#Text=Do not talk about /b/ ( Only applies to raids . )
#Text=Do NOT talk about /b/ ( eBaums did it . )
#Text=Both key rules were broken by users , according to Plasma .

#Text=The attack on Scientology was launched on Wednesday January 16 by a group labelled " Anonymous " , on the website " Insurgency Wiki " , a spinoff of 4chan which is also affiliated with 711chan .

#Text=The " History " section of the site explains , in a satirical fashion , that the incident was prompted by the Church of Scientology 's attempts to remove a promotional video featuring Scientologist Tom Cruise from YouTube .
#Text=Though YouTube complied with the Church of Scientology 's requests to take down the video , other sites such as Gawker.com stated that they will keep hosting the video .
#Text=One poster admitted to being a part of the effort , writing in a blog post " I have myself , as per instructions , loaded up Gigaloader and started bombarding the Scientology homepage .

#Text= The next morning I wake up to hundreds of MSN windows and emails telling me both servers have been compromised again , and our backups for 711 have been removed .

column1: #Text=I took a look at one of the things they planted on my machine , which lead me to # ! !regime on GameSurge IRC .
#Text=` immortal ' and about 30 drones were in that channel .

#Text=Members of the g00ns community ( allies of 711 , also linked to Partyvan IRC ) found out they had dox ( documents such as phone numbers , addresses , SSN numbers , names , that sort of thing ) on ` immortal ' and his wife .
#Text=I actually have these details and attempted to call him , but it went unanswered , " said Plasma .
